{
 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "ca6faffd-32ed-4c32-9921-e424c7a01464",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Field line following (J-TEXT)\n",
    "============================="
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "7aea8032-2ea7-4cdd-9321-ddca1e3592de",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import fusionsc as fsc\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pyvista as pv\n",
    "\n",
    "from fusionsc.devices import jtext"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "33e8e867-de71-46bd-8735-275f1b833f6e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pv.set_jupyter_backend('static')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f5e454a6-c699-475a-aa7d-d57f0fa034c8",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We use a 2D equilibrium as a baseline field"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "f7c574a0-fa10-42d5-a28d-9d3e6e793886",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "efitExample = jtext.exampleGeqdsk()\n",
    "field = fsc.magnetics.MagneticConfig.fromEFit(efitExample).compute(jtext.defaultGrid())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a4c40e76-7846-41c3-911f-ea94584c5971",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Let's follow a field line (which gives us position and field values)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "77f4813e-b284-43b9-9859-667a05b9ad73",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "Help on AsyncMethodDescriptor in module fusionsc.flt:\n",
      "\n",
      "followFieldlines(points, config, recordEvery=1, **kwargs) -> Any\n",
      "            Follows magnetic field lines.\n",
      "            \n",
      "            Mostly equivalent to :code:`(lambda x: return x[\"fieldLines\"], x[\"fieldStrengths\"])(trace(points, config, recordEvery, **kwargs))`.\n",
      "            \n",
      "            Parameters:\n",
      "                    - points: Starting points for the trace. Can be any shape, but the first dimension must have a size of 3 (x, y, z).\n",
      "                    - config: Magnetic configuration. If this is not yet computed, you also need to specify the 'grid' parameter.\n",
      "                    - recordEvery: Number of tracing steps between each recorded point.\n",
      "    \n",
      "            Returns:\n",
      "                    A tuple holding:\n",
      "                    - An array of shape `points.shape     + [max. field line length]` indicating the field line point locations\n",
      "                    - An array of shape `points.shape[1:] + [max. field line length]` indicating the field strength at those points\n",
      "            \n",
      "    *Note* Has :ref:`asynchronous variant<Asynchronous Function>` '.asnc(...)' that returns Promise[...]\n",
      "\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "help(fsc.flt.followFieldlines)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "68ad8028-cc5c-46f1-a6d7-a30f52f59b08",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "startPoint = [1.2, 0, 0]\n",
    "fieldLine, b = fsc.flt.followFieldlines(startPoint, field, recordEvery = 10, stepSize = 0.01, turnLimit = 400)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "92898364-565a-4675-9a32-dc72514b307b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Now we run Poincar√© plots for a few different cases"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "e45c70a7-5020-4877-89be-b19b1152aa3c",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "cloud = pv.PolyData(fieldLine.T)\n",
    "cloud.point_data['B'] = b\n",
    "\n",
    "pv.plot(cloud)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "5947914e-07b0-4134-a9f1-358f25969c19",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "We can also interpolate a surface from the provided points. *Note:* This is a function provided by PyVista."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "9272281d-3f1c-435a-95bd-f51f2afc25b7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<PIL.Image.Image image mode=RGB size=1024x768>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "surf = cloud.reconstruct_surface().interpolate(cloud)\n",
    "pv.plot(surf)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "id": "afd73e53-f187-4b51-a8b5-9c54660b2dca",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": []
  }
